<br>
There is a thread over on eqdiva about doing this but I'll explain it here anyway.  Although with the current nerf to charm kiting I don't know if it is possible anymore...<br>
<br>
Stoneleer Cocatrices make the best pets, but just about anything works.  Take your pet into the canyon and have it attack a scorpikis.  You might eat the HT, you may not.  It is only about 300 HP so you will probably be able to survive two and limp away.  Do NOT try charm kiting 2 Scorpikis, the chance of getting hit with 2 Harm Touches in a row is too great.  You will only die this way.<br>
<br>
Head out of the pit as soon as you can and kite it next to the canyon.  Keep killing them until a scrounger spawns.  They can spawn in any spot so just be patient.  I got one coin in 20 minutes, and then waited several hours for another (which I traded to get other coins).<br>
<br>
Remember that NPC SKs have a HT that refreshes every 5 minutes or so.  Stay at full health and kill them fast.<br>
<br>
Optional methods:<br>
<br>
I was able to figure out how to get the named ones to go after the little ones.  I won't tell you exactly how because it is probably considered an exploit, but it has something to do with which pet you use.  It is only really usefull if you get into big trouble because you'll probably want to be killing the scorps for xp while you are there.<br>
<br>
One time I got to the pit and there was another group trying to get a coin.  I had a scrounger on tracking but it was DEEP inside the pit (I'm talking inside one of the temples down there).  If you watch the pathing and time it right it is posible to pull from just about anywhere in there.  Of course you'll probably take a HT or two and will need a group waiting to kill your pull.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
